      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Substantive due process serves as a vital bulwark against the tyranny of the majority by insulating individual liberties from popular political whims. It allows the judiciary to safeguard fundamental rights when elected legislatures, driven by temporary majority sentiment, might otherwise erode those protections. Because the Constitution guarantees certain core rights, this concept empowers judges to act as a necessary check, ensuring that majority rule does not become a license for oppression. This judicial review protects minority rights from being trampled by the will of the majority.",
      "source": "target",
